member.summary:
            IRegistryID is a interface used in DBRegistry. It encapsulates ID, DefaultValue, and NewValue.
            An example of using IRegistryID interface to access DBRegistry is as below.

AutoCount.Data.DBRegistry reg = AutoCount.Data.DBRegistry.Create(dbSetting);

reg.GetValue(new AutoCount.RegistryID.AccountCodeFormat());

reg.SetValue(new AutoCount.RegistryID.AccountCodeFormat("AAA-AAAA"));
